"{\"uid\": \"thewrap.com-turkish-olympic-shooter-viral-silver-glasses-hand-pocket\", \"text\": \"With one hand in his pants pocket, Yusuf Dike\\u00e7 \\\"casually\\\" scored Turkey's first-ever olympic medal for shooting  Olympic target shooting historically does not get much attention at most Summer Games -\\u00a0until pistol marksman Yusuf Dike\\u00e7 and his \\\"insane aura\\\" came along.  The Turkish athlete went viral after winning silver in the team competition -\\u00a0 with one hand in his pocket and what appeared to be a pair of reading glasses, as opposed to his competitors who sport cyborg-like specs and other specialty equipment. He insisted he did not need all the fancy gear to bring home some hardware.  \\\"I did not need special equipment. I am a natural, a natural shooter,\\\" Dikec told Turkish media.  In Olympic shooting, they use equipment like:> A lens to avoid blur> A lens for better precision> ear protectors for noiseThen a Turkish guy (Dike\\u00e7) came and won a silver medal with just a pair of GLASSES.pic.twitter.com/tobbeIifiS  Many sharpshooting competitors wear special glasses to obscure vision in one eye, which are allowed, and ear protection. Dike\\u00e7's casual, hand-in-his pocket approach took the internet by storm.  Dike\\u00e7 has been thrown into the public eye overnight and according to one X (formerly twitter) user, has become the \\\"most famous man on earth.\\\" Since the event, there have been countless memes and posts about the athlete.  \\\"This is what you call aura \\u2026 Yusuf Dikec of Turkey shows up without any specialist equipment for shooting, looking like he just came out of the crowd and gave it a go,\\\" LADibble wrote on X.  This is what you call aura51-year-old Yusuf Dikec of Turkey shows up without any specialist equipment for shooting, looking like he just came out of the crowd and gave it a go\\u2026 he just casually took home silver at the Olympics \\ud83e\\udee1pic.twitter.com/ANrB7PyfxP  Lots of people have been making jokes about Dike\\u00e7's casual nature in comparison  to his fellow Olympians, who went all out on their style and gear.  Gen Z vs Gen X \\ud83e\\udd23(Yusuf Dike\\u00e7 73)pic.twitter.com/wO3ibEx6rY  The 51-year-old has been patiently waiting for his moment to shine - he's competed at every Summer Olympics since 2008. This was Turkey's first-ever medal in Olympic shooting.  Dike\\u00e7 is not the only \\\"legend\\\" to come out of this year's shooting competitions. For completely opposite reasons, South Korea's Kim Yej went viral for her \\\"sci-fi\\\" looking attire and \\\"Main Character Energy.\\\"  \\\"This girl is a movie character like how is she real?\\\" another user posted on X.  Korean shooters are such badassHere is Kim Ye-ji casually breaking the world record and winning gold in#OlympicGamesLooks as if she is straight out of a Park Chan-wook movie \\ud83d\\ude06pic.twitter.com/jB6wDAEZTN  It's safe to say that these two have not only won olympic medals, but also the hearts of everyone on the internet.  I am assembling one last teamhttps://t.co/Llw1cO9EOfpic.twitter.com/jckD0P1Lfh\"}"